<title>IRC</title>
   <p>
      IRC stands for Internet Relay Chat. It is a real-time multi-user messaging
      system. You can get help and advice on the Endless IRC server from other
      Endless users and developers.
   </p>
   <p>
      To connect to the Endless IRC server, use <app>empathy</app> or <app>xchat</app>,
      or use a web interface like <link href="http://chat.mibbit.com/">mibbit</link>.
   </p>
   <p>
      To create an IRC account in empathy, see the
      <link href="help:empathy/irc-manage">Empathy documentation</link>.
   </p>
   <p>
      The Endless IRC server is <sys>irc.gnome.org</sys>. You may also see it referred to as the "GIMP network".
      If your computer is properly configured you can click on the link
      <link href="irc://irc.gnome.org/gnome" /> to access the <sys>gnome</sys> channel.
   </p>
   <p>
      While IRC being a real-time discussion, people tend to not reply immediately, so be patient.
   </p>
   <note>
      <p>Please note the <link href="https://live.gnome.org/CodeOfConduct/">Endless code of conduct</link>
      applies when you chat on IRC.</p>
   </note>
